      "content": "idk it feels more specific than just a glitch. like, every time i'm about to make a big decision, the low end in the songs just... shifts. almost like a rhythmic sub-frequency that isn't actually part of the song. do you think there's a way to actually detect if there are extra frequencies being layered into a digital stream like that? like a way to see if the audio data is being messed with?",
